<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very similar vegetatively to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suburceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea suburceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but easily distinguished by the funnel-shaped corolla with a well-developed entire limb. It has often been misidentified as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="batatoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. batatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the leaf shape and inflorescence structure, the flowers often being borne on leafy side shoots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
